#Text=The New Orleans Pelicans took down the Philadelphia 76ers , 131 - 124 , at Smoothie King Center on Sunday .
#Text=New Orleans ( 14 - 13 ) saw a well - balanced approach to offense in Sunday 's win , as six players scored in double figures .
#Text=Leading the team with 29 points was superstar big man Anthony Davis , who shot an impressive 11 - of - 19 from the field .
#Text=The team as a whole was highly efficient , shooting a stunning 58 percent from the floor on the night .
#Text=The game was also one of veteran point guard Rajon Rondo 's strongest showings in a Pelicans uniform , as he recorded a season - high 18 assists to go along with 13 points and five steals .
#Text=Rondo took charge of the Pelicans offense effectively , contributing to the team 's impressive 33 total assists .
#Text=Philadelphia ( 13 - 14 ) was without star big man Joel Embiid , who was a late scratch due to back tightness before the game .
#Text=Despite Embiid 's absence , the team still managed to excel on the offensive end .
#Text=Rookie ball handler Ben Simmons took on a large role on offense , scoring 27 points and dished out ten assists .
#Text=Veteran sharpshooter J.J.
#Text=Redick added an additional 28 points and shot a stellar 8 - of - 14 from the field .
#Text=That included three three - pointers , making up a third of the nine made by the team on the night .
#Text=The Pelicans will visit Houston on Monday , while the 76ers will see Minnesota on Tuesday .
